{"batch":"Abstractions & Dependencies","batch_index":1,"assessments":{"abstraction_fitness":73.8},"dimension_notes":{"abstraction_fitness":{"evidence":["`goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go` defines many function-field bags (`RuntimeContainerOps`, `RuntimeUrbitOps`, `RuntimeSnapshotOps`, etc.) that are mostly direct pass-throughs to package functions in `defaultRuntime*` constructors.","`goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_docker.go` repeats the same dependency wiring pattern (`newDockerRuntime`, `newUrbitRuntime`, `newWireguardRuntime`) with additional alias layers (`type dockerRuntimeContextOps = RuntimeContextOps`, etc.), increasing indirection without adding policy.","`goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go` repeatedly re-creates and re-defaults `workflowRuntime` for small wrappers (`persistShip*`, `AreSubdomainsAliases`, `RunTransitionedOperation`), producing wrapper chains rather than stable boundary objects.","`goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go` contains callback-per-method runtime structs (`startupInitRuntime`, `startupBootstrapRuntime`, `startBackgroundServicesRuntime`) with repeated nil-check boilerplate methods, indicating seam sprawl.","`goseg/structs/configs.go` keeps a very wide `SysConfig` aggregate with unrelated domains (auth sessions, update strategy, wireguard flags, backup state, Penpai, disk warnings), while `goseg/config/config_update_schema.go` encodes many field-specific patch handlers against the same aggregate, reinforcing broad config-bag coupling across modules like `main`, `collectors`, `importer`, and startup orchestration."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","confidence":"high","sub_axes":{"abstraction_leverage":69.5,"indirection_cost":74.0,"interface_honesty":77.8}},"findings":[{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"runtime_seam_sprawl_without_policy","summary":"Runtime seam structs are replicated across subsystems as function-pointer bags that mainly forward calls, creating high indirection with little behavioral leverage.","related_files":["goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go","goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_docker.go","goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go","goseg/rectify/rectify.go","goseg/importer/importer.go","goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go"],"evidence":["`runtime_ops.go` and `runtime_docker.go` both build large default runtime structs mapping almost 1:1 to package functions (`config.*`, `StartContainer`, `networkRuntime.*`).","`shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go` defines multiple embedded runtime structs and repeatedly calls `defaultWorkflowRuntime()` + `withDefaultsWorkflowRuntime()` in many exported helpers, adding wrapper depth for simple calls.","`rectify.go`, `importer.go`, and `startup_orchestrator.go` repeat the same pattern: define runtime struct of callbacks, default constructor, nil-guard methods, then shallow wrappers over the callbacks."],"suggestion":"Introduce a smaller set of cohesive service interfaces per domain (for example: `ContainerService`, `ConfigService`, `TransitionPublisher`) and inject those once at subsystem construction. Replace per-function callback bags with boundary objects that own policy, and remove repeated `default*Runtime()` wrapper entrypoints by consolidating to a single explicit composition root.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"overgrown_runtime_injection_pattern"},{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"global_sysconfig_param_bag_coupling","summary":"A single broad `SysConfig` abstraction acts as a cross-domain parameter bag, forcing unrelated modules to couple to one mutable aggregate.","related_files":["goseg/structs/configs.go","goseg/config/config_update_schema.go","goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go","goseg/broadcast/collectors/collectors.go","goseg/main.go","goseg/importer/importer.go"],"evidence":["`structs.SysConfig` includes many unrelated concerns (sessions/auth, update settings, wireguard state, backups, disk warnings, Penpai, network mode) in one model.","`config_update_schema.go` contains a long field-by-field patch registry operating on `*structs.SysConfig`, indicating update logic is bound to a monolithic bag rather than bounded settings aggregates.","Other modules consume slices of this bag via multiple snapshots (`SwapSettingsSnapshot`, `StartramSettingsSnapshot`, `ConnectivitySettingsSnapshot`, etc.), showing ongoing decomposition pressure around a central wide config abstraction."],"suggestion":"Split persisted configuration into bounded aggregates (for example runtime context, auth/session state, network/wireguard, update policy, AI/Penpai settings) with separate storage/update paths. Keep `SysConfig` only as legacy serialization boundary if needed, but move internal APIs and patch schema to typed aggregate-specific updaters.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"monolithic_configuration_model"},{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"dual_entrypoint_wrapper_duplication","summary":"Paired `X`/`XWithContext` and `defaultRuntime` wrappers duplicate orchestration flow across packages, increasing surface area without meaningful abstraction gain.","related_files":["goseg/routines/version.go","goseg/routines/system/system.go","goseg/rectify/rectify.go","goseg/importer/importer.go","goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go"],"evidence":["`routines/version.go` and `routines/system/system.go` duplicate entrypoints (`Start*` + `Start*WithContext`, `CheckVersionLoop` + `CheckVersionLoopWithContext`) where non-context variants are thin context.Background wrappers.","`rectify.go` similarly duplicates handlers with and without context (`UrbitTransitionHandler`, `UrbitTransitionHandlerWithContext`, `SystemTransitionHandler`, etc.).","`importer.go` and `operations_runtime.go` repeat default-runtime forwarding helpers (`foo()` -> `fooForRuntime(defaultRuntime())`) across many functions, expanding API footprint while preserving same behavior."],"suggestion":"Standardize on context-first internal APIs and keep only minimal compatibility shims at package boundaries. Collapse repetitive `defaultRuntime` forwarding into one exported constructor-based service per package so call sites use one path and tests inject runtime once.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"overgrown_runtime_injection_pattern"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Testing seam strategy evolved into callback-per-function runtime bags instead of cohesive boundary services.","Configuration responsibilities accumulated in one serialized root model and leaked into many packages.","Backward-compatible wrapper layering was added incrementally without pruning old entrypoints."],"likely_symptoms":["runtime_seam_sprawl_without_policy","dual_entrypoint_wrapper_duplication"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}


